OL,6,F"However, this case demonstrates that
OL,7,Fallegations of misconduct will be
OL,8,Frobustly investigated and that
OL,9,Fofficers will be held to account, all
OL,10,Fof which contributes positively to
OL,11,Fpublic confidence in policing."
OL,13,FFollowing the conclusion of the Police
OL,14,FOmbudsman investigation, a file was
OL,15,Fsubmitted to the Public Prosecution
OL,16,FService (PPS) in relation to the
OL,17,Fpotential offences of Misconduct in
OL,18,FPublic Office and sending grossly
OL,19,Foffensive messages contrary to the
OL,20,FCommunications Act (2003).
